        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-12-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1291" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1291">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.6331/12–649: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-12-06">December 6,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received December 6—8:29 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2210. Ward states was asked yesterday (December 5) by local authorities for
                    recent deeds or leases (uncertain which) for two pieces <pb facs="1052" n="1042" xml:id="pg_1042"/> Government real estate Mukden. When Ward stated believed
                    title deeds in Washington, was informed US Government ownership would not be
                    recognized.</p>
                <p>Ward has had no further contact with Steventon, British pro-Consul Mukden, re
                    takeover property.</p>
                <p>Bryners now removing personal property and moveable Government property.</p>
                <p>Tientsin by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
